                    <div class="section" id="what_is_dei">
                        <div class="section-header"><h3>WHAT IS DEI?</h3></div>
                        <div class="section-content"><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div style="position: relative; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>INTRODUCTION TO DEI</h4><div><p>DEI stands for <b>Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion</b>. These three concepts work together to create workplaces where everyone can thrive, contribute their best, and feel valued for who they are.</p><p>As a team leader, understanding DEI is not just about compliance or ticking boxes. It is about creating an environment where your team members feel respected, supported, and able to do their best work.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>Why does DEI matter for team leaders?</b></p><p>When you understand and apply DEI principles, you:</p><ul><li>Build stronger, more resilient teams</li><li>Make fairer decisions about opportunities and recognition</li><li>Create an environment where people feel safe to share ideas</li><li>Reduce conflict and misunderstanding</li><li>Support your organisation's legal and ethical responsibilities</li></ul><p>In the following sections, we will explore each component of DEI in plain English, with practical examples you can relate to in your workplace.</p></div></div></div>
                        <div class="navigation-buttons">
