                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="0" style="display: block;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q1: What does DEI stand for?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>Diversity, Engagement, and Integration</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>Development, Equality, and Innovation</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>Diversity, Equality, and Involvement</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> DEI stands for Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion. These three pillars work together to create workplaces where everyone can thrive. Diversity is about representation, Equity is about fair access and opportunity, and Inclusion is about creating belonging.</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> DEI stands for <b>Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion</b>. Remember: Diversity recognises differences, Equity ensures fair access to opportunities, and Inclusion creates a sense of belonging for all.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'B')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="1" style="display: none;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q2: What is the key difference between Equity and Equality?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>They mean exactly the same thing</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>Equality gives everyone the same resources; Equity gives people what they need to succeed</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>Equity is about legal rights; Equality is about fairness</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>Equality is more important than Equity in the workplace</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> While Equality provides the same resources to everyone, Equity recognises that people have different starting points and needs. Equity means providing tailored support so everyone has a fair chance to succeed.</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> The key difference is that <b>Equality gives everyone the same resources, while Equity gives people what they specifically need to succeed</b>. Equity acknowledges that people start from different positions and may need different levels of support.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'B')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="2" style="display: none;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q3: Which of the following is an example of Affinity Bias?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>A manager favouring a team member who went to the same university as them</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>Judging someone based on the first piece of information you learned about them</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>Assuming someone is competent because they are tall</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>Remembering recent events more clearly than past events</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> Affinity Bias is our tendency to favour people who are similar to us - whether that's sharing the same background, interests, education, or experiences. This bias can lead to less diverse teams and unfair advantages for those who are "like us."</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> Affinity Bias is when we <b>favour people who are similar to us</b>. The example of a manager favouring someone from the same university demonstrates this. Option B describes Anchoring Bias, C describes the Halo Effect, and D describes Recency Bias.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'A')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="3" style="display: none;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q4: What is Confirmation Bias?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>The tendency to favour people who confirm their attendance at meetings</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>The tendency to seek out information that supports our existing beliefs while ignoring contradictory evidence</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>The tendency to confirm decisions with multiple people before acting</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>The tendency to confirm stereotypes about other groups</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> Confirmation Bias leads us to notice and remember information that confirms what we already believe, while overlooking evidence that contradicts it. As a leader, this can cause you to miss important feedback or unfairly evaluate team members based on pre-existing opinions.</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> Confirmation Bias is <b>our tendency to seek out and favour information that supports our existing beliefs while ignoring contradictory evidence</b>. This can lead to unfair judgements and missed opportunities to learn new perspectives.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'B')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="4" style="display: none;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q5: Which behaviour demonstrates inclusive leadership?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>Making decisions quickly without consulting the team to show strong leadership</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>Treating everyone exactly the same regardless of their individual needs</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>Actively seeking diverse perspectives and creating space for all voices to be heard</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>Focusing only on high performers and giving them more opportunities</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> Inclusive leaders actively seek diverse perspectives, ensure all team members have opportunities to contribute, and create psychological safety where people feel comfortable sharing ideas. This approach leads to better decisions and a more engaged team.</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> Inclusive leadership means <b>actively seeking diverse perspectives and creating space for all voices to be heard</b>. This involves recognising individual needs, inviting contribution from quieter team members, and valuing different viewpoints.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'C')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="5" style="display: none;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q6: What should an inclusive leader do when they notice a team member being talked over in meetings?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>Wait until after the meeting to address it privately with both parties</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>Intervene in the moment by redirecting back to the person who was interrupted</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>Assume the interrupted person can speak up for themselves if they want to</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>Ignore it as it is a normal part of group dynamics</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> Inclusive leaders actively facilitate fair participation. Intervening in the moment - for example, by saying "Let's hear what Sarah was saying" - demonstrates that all contributions are valued and models inclusive behaviour for the whole team.</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> The best approach is to <b>intervene in the moment by redirecting back to the person who was interrupted</b>. This demonstrates that you value their contribution and models inclusive behaviour. While follow-up conversations can help, in-the-moment action has greater impact.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'B')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="quiz-question-wrapper" data-question-index="6" style="display: none;">
                                    <h4 class="quiz-question-text">Q7: How does inclusion contribute to organisational sustainability?</h4>
                                    <div class="quiz-options">
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="A" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>A</span><p>It reduces costs by requiring fewer HR policies</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="B" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>B</span><p>Inclusive cultures attract and retain talent, drive innovation through diverse thinking, and build resilient teams that adapt to change</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="C" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>C</span><p>It has no direct connection to sustainability - they are separate business priorities</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="quiz-option" data-value="D" onclick="this.parentElement.querySelectorAll('.quiz-option').forEach(o => o.classList.remove('selected')); this.classList.add('selected');">
                                            <span>D</span><p>Inclusion only matters for meeting legal compliance requirements</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-feedback-wrapper">
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback correct"><p><strong>Correct!</strong> Inclusive cultures create sustainable organisations by attracting diverse talent, reducing turnover, fostering innovation through varied perspectives, and building psychologically safe teams that can adapt and thrive through change. This is why DEI is increasingly seen as a strategic business priority, not just a "nice to have."</p></div>
                                        <div class="quiz-feedback incorrect"><p><strong>Not quite.</strong> Inclusion directly contributes to sustainability because <b>inclusive cultures attract and retain talent, drive innovation through diverse thinking, and build resilient teams</b>. Organisations with strong inclusion see lower turnover, better problem-solving, and greater adaptability - all essential for long-term success.</p></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="quiz-nav">
                                        <button class="quiz-check-btn" onclick="checkQuizAnswer(this, 'B')">Check Answer</button>
                                        <button class="quiz-next-btn" style="display: none;" onclick="nextQuizQuestion(this)">Next Question</button>
